# Backend Build — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

12 production-ready files for the ML-Augmented Traffic Routing System.

---

## Windows Run Commands (in exact order)

### Step 1 — Create & activate virtual environment
```powershell
cd "C:\Users\KIIT0001\OneDrive\Desktop\Traffic-Congestion-Analysis-and-Routing--main"
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```
**Expected output:**
```
(.venv) PS C:\...\Traffic-Congestion-Analysis-and-Routing--main>
```

---

### Step 2 — Install dependencies
```powershell
pip install -r backend\requirements.txt
```
**Expected output:**
```
Successfully installed fastapi-0.115.0 uvicorn-... xgboost-2.1.1 ...
```

---

### Step 3 — Copy env template and configure
```powershell
Copy-Item backend\.env.example backend\.env
```
Then open `backend\.env` and set:
- `MODEL_BACKEND=xgboost_json`
- `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./serviceAccountKey.json`

---

