---

### Step 6 — Start the FastAPI server
```powershell
cd backend
python -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload
```
**Expected output:**
```
{"time": "...", "level": "INFO", "logger": "predictor", "message": "XGBoost model loaded from ..."}
{"time": "...", "level": "INFO", "logger": "firestore_client", "message": "Firebase Admin SDK initialised successfully."}
{"time": "...", "level": "INFO", "logger": "scheduler", "message": "Scheduler configured: interval=30s, timezone=IST"}
{"time": "...", "level": "INFO", "logger": "main", "message": "...\"message\": \"Model loaded. Scheduler started.\""}
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000 (Press CTRL+C to quit)
```

---

### Step 7 — Verify the health endpoint
```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri http://localhost:8000/health
```
**Expected output:**
```json
{
  "status": "ok",
  "model_version": "xgboost:1741867XXX",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-13T09:12:45.123456+00:00"
}
```

---

### Step 8 — Test single junction prediction
```powershell
$body = @{
  junction_id = "JN001"
  features = @{
    vehicle_count = 350
    queue_length = 420.5
    traffic_density = 85.3
    avg_speed = 18.2
    waiting_time = 180.0
    green_signal_ratio = 0.45
    monsoon_active = 1
    peak_hour = 1
  }
} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri http://localhost:8000/predict -Method Post `
  -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body
```
**Expected output:**
```json
{
  "junction_id": "JN001",
  "predicted_delay_sec": 245.312,
  "congestion_level": "HIGH",
  "top_factors": [
    { "feature_name": "waiting_time",    "importance_score": 0.312 },
    { "feature_name": "traffic_density", "importance_score": 0.228 },
    { "feature_name": "vehicle_count",   "importance_score": 0.195 }
  ],
  "inference_ms": 2.847,
  "model_version": "xgboost:1741867XXX"
}
```

