Open in browser after starting server:
- **Swagger UI**: http://localhost:8000/docs
- **ReDoc**:      http://localhost:8000/redoc

---

## Potential Errors & Fixes

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `cannot be loaded because running scripts is disabled` | PowerShell ExecutionPolicy | Run: `Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser RemoteSigned` |
| `FileNotFoundError: traffic_model.json` | Training not run yet | Run Step 4 then Step 5 first |
| `Firebase 503` | Missing `serviceAccountKey.json` | Download from Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service accounts |
| `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'xgboost'` | venv not activated | Run `.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1` |
| `Port 8000 already in use` | Another process on port | Change port: `--port 8001` or kill process: `netstat -ano \| findstr :8000` |
| `onnxruntime not found` if `MODEL_BACKEND=onnx` | ONNX file missing | Run `MODEL_BACKEND=xgboost_json` until you export the ONNX model |
| `norm_params.json not found` warning | Training not complete | Run [train_xgboost.py](file:///C:/Users/KIIT0001/OneDrive/Desktop/Traffic-Congestion-Analysis-and-Routing--main/ml/training/train_xgboost.py) — it generates this file |

